---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';

const schema = [
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "Article",
    "headline": "Herman Miller Aeron vs Steelcase Leap Plus: For Tall People",
    "url": "https://tallchairadvisor.com/aeron-vs-leap-plus/",
    "image": "https://tallchairadvisor.com/images/og-default.jpg",
    "datePublished": "2025-01-15",
    "dateModified": "2026-03-01",
    "author": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "Tall Chair Advisor" },
    "publisher": {
      "@type": "Organization",
      "name": "Tall Chair Advisor",
      "logo": { "@type": "ImageObject", "url": "https://tallchairadvisor.com/images/og-default.jpg" }
    }
  },
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "BreadcrumbList",
    "itemListElement": [
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 1, "name": "Home", "item": "https://tallchairadvisor.com/" },
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 2, "name": "Best Office Chairs", "item": "https://tallchairadvisor.com/best-office-chairs/" },
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 3, "name": "Aeron vs Leap Plus", "item": "https://tallchairadvisor.com/aeron-vs-leap-plus/" }
    ]
  }
];
---

<Layout
  title="Aeron Size C vs Steelcase Leap Plus for Tall People | Tall Chair Advisor"
  description="Aeron Size C vs Steelcase Leap Plus compared for tall users. Fixed vs adjustable seat depth, lumbar support, and which handles users over 6'3&quot; better."
  ogType="article"
  schema={schema}
>
  <header class="py-12 md:py-16 lg:py-20 bg-secondary/30">
    <div class="container-article text-center">
      <h1 class="text-balance">Aeron Size C vs Steelcase Leap Plus</h1>
      <p class="mt-4 text-lg md:text-xl text-muted-foreground max-w-2xl mx-auto animate-slide-up">
        A direct comparison for tall users choosing between these two premium chairs
      </p>
    </div>
  </header>

  <article class="container-article py-12 md:py-16">
    <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg px-4 py-3 mb-8 text-sm text-amber-900">
      <strong>Disclosure:</strong> We may earn a commission from purchases made through links on this page. This never influences our evaluations.
      <a href="/affiliate-disclosure/" class="underline ml-1">Learn more →</a>
    </div>

    <div class="prose-tca">
      <section>
        <h2>Overview</h2>
        <p>
          Both the Herman Miller Aeron Size C and the Steelcase Leap Plus are popular ergonomic chairs for tall users,
          but they serve different body types and preferences. The Aeron Size C focuses on breathability and posture
          support for lean-to-average builds, while the Leap Plus is designed for larger users who need greater
          adjustability and higher weight capacity. This comparison breaks down the key differences in dimensions,
          fit, and overall suitability for tall users.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Dimensional Comparison</h2>
        <p>
          The Aeron Size C offers a fixed seat depth of approximately 18.5 inches and a seat height range of about 16
          to 20.5 inches, with a weight capacity up to 350 lbs. Its mesh construction prioritizes airflow and pressure
          distribution but limits depth adjustability. The Steelcase Leap Plus features an adjustable seat depth up to
          roughly 19.75 inches and a wider seat, with a seat height range of approximately 15.5 to 22.5 inches. It
          supports users up to 500 lbs, making it better suited for taller and heavier builds that require more flexibility.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>For Tall Users</h2>
        <p>
          For tall users with larger frames or those over 300 lbs, the Leap Plus generally provides better support due
          to its wider seat, deeper adjustability, and higher weight rating. It accommodates longer femurs and offers
          a broader range of ergonomic tuning. The Aeron Size C works well for tall users with leaner builds who value
          breathability and a firmer, more upright sitting posture. Its mesh design is especially appealing for users
          who sit for long hours and tend to run hot.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Verdict</h2>
        <p>
          Choose the Steelcase Leap Plus if you are a taller user with a larger or heavier build who needs maximum
          adjustability and long-term support. Choose the Herman Miller Aeron Size C if you are tall with a
          lean-to-average build and prioritize ventilation, posture support, and a lighter seating feel.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Read Full Reviews</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><a href="/review/aeron-size-c" class="link-internal">Herman Miller Aeron Size C Review</a></li>
          <li><a href="/review/leap-plus" class="link-internal">Steelcase Leap Plus Review</a></li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <div class="mt-8 pt-6 border-t border-border">
        <a href="/best-office-chairs" class="link-internal">← Back to Best Office Chairs for Tall People</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </article>
</Layout>
